    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "hey i'm looking at this contract for a freelance gig and i don't really get what this 'indemnification' part means. it sounds kinda scary. can u explain it in simple terms?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Indemnification, in simple terms, is like having a shield against a surprise bill from some messy business. It basically means one party agrees to cover the costs and any legal trouble if something goes wrong, usually if someone else gets sued because of what they did. Think of it as a promise to cover the damage if a particular situation turns into a big, scary mess. It's all about shifting the risk, which is important, especially when you're dealing with contracts.",
      "source": "target",
